	</header>

	<figure class="amp-wp-article-featured-image wp-caption">
	<amp-img width="702" height="527" src="https://borderbuddy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Blog-Photo-Layout-1024x768.png" class="attachment-large size-large wp-post-image amp-wp-enforced-sizes i-amphtml-layout-intrinsic i-amphtml-layout-size-defined" alt="A photo showing Shopify Help Center page about Activating third-party carrier-calculated shipping" srcset="https://borderbuddy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Blog-Photo-Layout.png 1024w, https://borderbuddy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Blog-Photo-Layout-300x225.png 300w, https://borderbuddy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Blog-Photo-Layout-768x576.png 768w, https://borderbuddy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Blog-Photo-Layout-320x240.png 320w" sizes="(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px" data-hero-candidate="" layout="intrinsic" disable-inline-width="" data-hero i-amphtml-ssr i-amphtml-layout="intrinsic"><i-amphtml-sizer slot="i-amphtml-svc" class="i-amphtml-sizer"><img alt="" aria-hidden="true" class="i-amphtml-intrinsic-sizer" role="presentation" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyBoZWlnaHQ9IjUyNyIgd2lkdGg9IjcwMiIgeG1sbnM9Imh0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnIiB2ZXJzaW9uPSIxLjEiLz4="></i-amphtml-sizer><img class="i-amphtml-fill-content i-amphtml-replaced-content" decoding="async" loading="lazy" alt="A photo showing Shopify Help Center page about Activating third-party carrier-calculated shipping" src="https://borderbuddy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Blog-Photo-Layout-1024x768.png" srcset="https://borderbuddy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Blog-Photo-Layout.png 1024w, https://borderbuddy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Blog-Photo-Layout-300x225.png 300w, https://borderbuddy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Blog-Photo-Layout-768x576.png 768w, https://borderbuddy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Blog-Photo-Layout-320x240.png 320w" sizes="(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px"></amp-img>	</figure>

	<div class="amp-wp-article-content">
		<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Expanding your Shopify store beyond the U.S. into international markets like Canada can seem intimidating. How will you handle duties, taxes, customs clearance, and finding affordable shipping rates?</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Luckily, Shopify makes cross-border ecommerce much easier with its built-in support for carrier-calculated shipping. This allows you to tap into major carriers like UPS, FedEx, and DHL to instantly get real-time rate estimates at checkout.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">In this post, we’ll cover everything you need to know about activating carrier-calculated shipping on Shopify, including:</span></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Pricing to add carrier rates on different plans</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Steps to enable carrier calculated shipping</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Turning on rates for additional stores</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Getting support when you need it</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Let’s dive in!</span></p>
<h2><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Pricing to Add Carrier Rates on Shopify Plan</span></h2>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">On the basic Shopify plan, carrier-calculated rates from third parties like UPS are not enabled by default. However, you can add this capability for an additional $20 per month by upgrading your subscription.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">The Advanced and Plus Shopify plans include activating carrier rates for free without any extra fees needed. So upgrading to one of these upper tiers is another route to enabling the feature.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">If selling internationally to markets like Canada is a core part of your ecommerce strategy, the slightly higher cost of an Advanced plan can pay for itself quickly through the benefits of calculated shipping.</span></p>
<h2><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">How to Activate Carrier Rates on Shopify</span></h2>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Once you’ve added carrier calculated shipping to your Shopify subscription, it’s straightforward to toggle it on:</span></p>
<ol>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Navigate to Settings &gt; Shipping and Delivery in your Shopify admin.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Under “Carrier shipping”, click on “Enable” or “Upgrade your plan” if needed.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Select the shipping zone you want to add rates for. Often this will be a “Rest of World” zone for international orders.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Click “Add rate” and choose “Use carrier or app to calculate rates” when prompted.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Search for and select the carrier accounts you wish to use, like UPS, FedEx, or USPS.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Connect your carrier accounts by entering your account credentials when prompted.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">That’s it! Shopify will now pull in live shipping rates from those carriers at checkout anytime an international customer views shipping options to their destination. No more having to manually update static shipping prices.</span></p>
<h2><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Turning On Carrier Rates for New Stores</span></h2>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">If you want to activate carrier calculated shipping for additional new Shopify stores later on, you’ll need to follow a slightly different process. </span>It’s worth noting that this applies <strong>not only to new stores but to all stores below the Advanced Plan threshold</strong>.</p>
<p>Rather than enabling it directly from your store’s shipping settings, which notably lacks the toggle for the $20 option, you will have to get in touch with Shopify support. This can be done either through chat or email. Inform them that you wish to enable carrier rates for your store subscription, and they will assist in activating the feature swiftly.</p>
<p>This extra step is due to how carrier rate permissions function across store accounts.</p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Reaching out to Shopify support via a chat is often the quickest way to get carrier rates switched on for a new store. Usually you’ll be connected with an advisor within minutes who can enable it while you wait.</span></p>
<h2><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Getting Support When You Need It</span></h2>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Speaking of Shopify support, chatting with advisors is the best way to get assistance if you run into any hiccups setting up calculated shipping.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Here are some key benefits of using Shopify’s chat-based customer support:</span></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Instant 1-on-1 connection with knowledgeable shipping experts</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Ability to share screenshots to tackle configuration issues</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Guidance specific to your store’s setup and subscription tier</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">No need to refresh email repeatedly awaiting replies</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Of course, you can also reach Shopify support via email or phone if preferred. But chat is often the fastest, most effective option for solving time-sensitive issues.</span></p>
<h2><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Make Cross-Border Shipping to Canada a Breeze</span></h2>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Selling beyond U.S. borders can seem intimidating for Shopify merchants at first. But tools like carrier-calculated shipping rates make the process smooth and painless.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">With just a few clicks, you can tap into discounted shipping prices from top carriers optimized for international delivery. No more uncertainty or manual rate estimations needed.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Follow this guide to start activating carrier-calculated shipping on your Shopify store today. The additional global revenue it unlocks will quickly offset any extra monthly costs.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">So don’t let cross-border complexity stop you from expanding your ecommerce business north of the border. With the right tools and support, you can confidently ship worldwide and watch your international sales grow.</span></p>
<h2><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Making Cross-Border Shipping Easier with BorderBuddy</span></h2>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">While Shopify’s carrier-calculated shipping rates are a powerful tool for simplifying international sales, there’s still the hurdle of duties, taxes, and customs clearance when selling to countries like Canada. This is where BorderBuddy comes in.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">BorderBuddy is a third-party app designed to handle all the complexities of cross-border shipping, from calculating duties and taxes to taking care of customs clearance. You can even offer your Canadian customers a complete, landed cost at checkout, so there are no surprise fees upon delivery. It’s the ideal complement to Shopify’s carrier-calculated rates, especially for merchants who are focused on expanding into the Canadian market.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Why Choose BorderBuddy?</span></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><b>Certified Customs Brokers</b><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">: BorderBuddy has certified customs brokers who submit any and all duties and taxes to the government for your customers.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><b>Exclusive Carrier Partnerships</b><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">: As of now, BorderBuddy exclusively uses UPS for shipping, with plans to add FedEx to the list. USPS is not an option because they don’t allow any other customs brokers other than Canada Post to handle their shipments.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><b>Canadian Sales Optimization</b><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">: If you’re already making sales to Canada but want to improve the customer experience, BorderBuddy’s shipping rates include brokerage costs, making it easier to win over Canadian consumers.</span><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><br>
</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><b>Cost-Effective</b><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">: With BorderBuddy, you only pay per order, not per product. They pass along deeply discounted shipping rates, leveraging the massive buying power of their partners.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"><b>Flexible for U.S.-Based Suppliers</b><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">: Even if your business is based in Canada but your supplier is in the U.S., you can still utilize BorderBuddy by entering your supplier’s U.S. address as the ship-from location.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Adding BorderBuddy to your Shopify store can make a significant difference in customer satisfaction and your bottom line when shipping to Canada. It’s a must-have for any Shopify merchant serious about making their mark in the Canadian ecommerce space.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">You’ve got the tools and the know-how, so what’s holding you back? Whether it’s unlocking new carrier-calculated shipping options with Shopify or optimizing for the Canadian market with BorderBuddy, the world is literally your marketplace.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">So why wait? Take the leap and expand your Shopify store beyond U.S. borders today—you might just find your next loyal customer in the Great White North!</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Reach out today</span><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"> or go to the </span><a href="https://apps.shopify.com/canadacustomsduty"><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Shopify App</span></a><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc"> store to know more.</span></p>
<p><span data-amp-original-style="font-weight: 400;" class="amp-wp-fe3f5cc">Start your global ecommerce journey now, and watch your international sales grow. You’ve got this!</span></p>

